The paper deals with anomaly detection in attributed graphs, which is a problem that falls under the intersection of several sub-fields in computer science. The most likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), as the paper deals with graph analysis and anomaly detection. The second likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), as the paper proposes a new quality measure for neighborhoods and presents a novel approach for anomaly mining. The third likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper uses optimization techniques to maximize the proposed measure. The fourth likely category is cs.DB (Databases), as the paper deals with processing graphs with millions of attributes. The fifth likely category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), as the paper proposes a new approach for anomaly detection that utilizes both structure and attributes.
